commentary: Aizaz Cheema to Sangakkara, FOUR runs edged between keeper and slip! Why on earth is Misbah economising on his slip fielders? He got away with it once when Taranga edged to Younis, but Sanga finds the gap perfectly. Length ball on middle and leg, angling away at pace, gets the edge at a nice catchable height ... There's little more the bowler can do.

commentary: Shahid Afridi to Perera, OUT Afridi goes one better by taking five wickets! Perera went for the mighty slog and got a top edge, it was in the air for an hour but it was Akmal who got under it. An incredible Pakistan fightback, reminiscent from the 1990s and earlier, and quite an unbelievable collapse by SL
